  "text": "The binding subunit of the IL-11 receptor has been recently cloned and shown to interact with gp130 but not with LIFR␤ [CITATION_1] 45) . In line with this observation, we found that tyrosine phosphorylated ␤ subunits could not be precipitated with the LIFR␤ antibody in IL-11-stimulated stromal/osteoblastic cells. In fact, our results strongly suggest that IL-11 induces homodimerization and tyrosine phosphorylation of gp130, since only a single band corresponding to gp130 was immunoprecipitated by the anti-gp130 antibody.",
